01:48:25,249 --> 01:48:29,919
and those who harvest their crops
with a machine and state subsidies?

983
01:48:36,427 --> 01:48:38,887
Let's be responsible consumers.

984
01:48:38,971 --> 01:48:41,139
Think about what we buy.

985
01:48:42,975 --> 01:48:45,727
It's too late to be a pessimist.

986
01:48:45,811 --> 01:48:48,146
I have seen agriculture
on a human scale.

987
01:48:48,230 --> 01:48:53,276
It can feed the whole planet if meat production
doesn't take the food out of people's mouths.

988
01:48:53,360 --> 01:48:57,363
I have seen fishermen
who take care what they catch...

989
01:48:57,448 --> 01:48:59,908
and care for the riches of the ocean.

990
01:49:01,118 --> 01:49:04,037
I have seen houses
producing their own energy.

991
01:49:04,121 --> 01:49:08,208
5,000 people live in the world's
first ever eco-friendly district,

992
01:49:08,292 --> 01:49:10,210
in Freiburg, Germany.

993
01:49:10,294 --> 01:49:12,253
Other cities partner the project.

994
01:49:12,338 --> 01:49:15,506
Mumbai is the thousandth to join them.

995
01:49:18,469 --> 01:49:22,388
The governments of New Zealand,
Iceland, Austria, Sweden...

996
01:49:22,473 --> 01:49:24,724
and other nations
have made the development...

997
01:49:24,808 --> 01:49:28,102
of renewable energy sources
a top priority.

998
01:49:28,187 --> 01:49:31,898
I know that 80% of the energy
we consume...

999
01:49:31,982 --> 01:49:34,234
comes from fossil energy sources.

1000
01:49:34,318 --> 01:49:39,572
Every week, two new coal-fired generating
plants are built in China alone.

1001
01:49:39,657 --> 01:49:42,242
But I have also seen, in Denmark,

1002
01:49:42,326 --> 01:49:44,911
a prototype of a coal-fired plant...

1003
01:49:44,995 --> 01:49:48,748
that releases its carbon
into the soil rather than the air.

1004
01:49:48,832 --> 01:49:51,459
A solution for the future?
Nobody knows yet.

1005
01:49:52,670 --> 01:49:54,587
I have seen, in Iceland,

1006
01:49:54,672 --> 01:49:59,467
an electricity plant powered
by the Earth's heat— geothermal power.

1007
01:49:59,551 --> 01:50:02,595
I have seen a sea snake
lying on the swell...

1008
01:50:02,680 --> 01:50:06,849
to absorb the energy of the waves
and produce electricity.

1009
01:50:11,021 --> 01:50:13,982
I have seen wind farms
off the coast of Denmark...

1010
01:50:14,066 --> 01:50:17,777
that produce 20%
of the country's electricity.

1011
01:50:17,861 --> 01:50:21,823
The U.S.A., China, India,
Germany and Spain...

1012
01:50:21,907 --> 01:50:25,118
are the biggest investors
in renewable energy.

1013
01:50:25,202 --> 01:50:29,038
They have already created over
two and a half million jobs.

1014
01:50:29,123 --> 01:50:32,542
Where on Earth doesn't the wind blow?

1015
01:50:34,086 --> 01:50:39,465
I have seen desert expanses
baking in the sun.

1016
01:50:39,550 --> 01:50:41,634
Everything on Earth is linked,

1017
01:50:41,719 --> 01:50:46,139
and the Earth is linked to the sun,
its original energy source.

1018
01:50:46,223 --> 01:50:50,018
Can humans not imitate plants
and capture its energy?

1019
01:50:50,102 --> 01:50:53,187
In one hour,
the sun gives the Earth...

1020
01:50:53,272 --> 01:50:58,818
the same amount of energy as that
consumed by all humanity in one year.

1021
01:50:58,902 --> 01:51:03,740
As long as the Earth exists,
the sun's energy will be inexhaustible.

1022
01:51:03,824 --> 01:51:08,328
All we have to do is stop drilling
the Earth and start looking to the sky.

1023
01:51:08,412 --> 01:51:11,748
All we have to do
is learn to cultivate the sun.

1024
01:51:11,832 --> 01:51:17,378
All these experiments are only examples,
but they testify to a new awareness.

1025
01:51:17,463 --> 01:51:20,923
They lay down markers
for a new human adventure...

1026
01:51:21,008 --> 01:51:25,261
based on moderation,
intelligence and sharing.

